title: High school sports report for Oct. 19
text: High school sports report for Oct. 19 Comment Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 12:08 AM By Times-Reporter staff report Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 12:08 AM VOLLEYBALL Claymont, Dover, Carrollton advance in sectionals Caitlin Clarke recorded 14 kills and 12 digs and Keanna Avery added six kills, seven blocks and seven digs as Claymont knocked off visiting St. Clairsville 25-15, 26-24, 25-12 in a Division II sectional tournament opener Monday night. The Mustangs (18-5) will play at Maysville for a sectional championship at 6 p.m. Thursday. • Sawyer Campbell scored 10 points with four aces, 16 assist and six digs as Dover knocked off host Buckeye Local 25-10, 25-12, 25-12 in Division II sectional tournament play. The Tornadoes (10-13) will play at West Holmes on Thursday. • Ali Poole recorded 26 digs, 18 kills and 11 points as Carrollton outlasted host River View 19-25, 26-24, 25-22, 17-25, 15-13 in the Division II sectional at Warsaw. • In Division IV sectional action, Shadyside eliminated Hiland three sets to two to advance to play Steubenville Catholic Central on Thursday. GIRLS SOCCER Emily Shalosky’s goal in the second overtime period gave Dover a thrilling 5-4 shootout win over host Steubenville in the Division II sectional tournament. The contest was tied at 1-1 at the end of regulation as Natalie Baker tallied for the Tornadoes (4-9-4) with an assist going to Grace Castercone. Peyton Frankovich and Raya Harrison scored in the first overtime on penalty kicks, while Mary Miller-Eschelman and Shalosky tallied in the second overtime. Trinity Thompson claimed the victory in goal for the Tornadoes. Dover will play at River View on Wednesday at 6 p.m. in a final. • Host Marlington ousted Fairless 3-2 in a Division III sectional contest. Alley Leeman scored twice for the Falcons. BOYS SOCCER Josh Ragon scored twice and had two assists and Tyler Boyd had the shutout in goal as host Tusky Valley blanked Caldwell 5-0 in a Division III sectional opener. The Trojans (9-5-3) will play at Hiland on Saturday. • Derek Miller scored twice, Ben Beachy added a goal and two assists and Derek Burke and Isaiah Yoder combined for the shutout as Hiland rolled over visiting Union Local 10-0. The Hawks (12-5-0) will host Tusky Valley on Saturday. By Times-Reporter staff report
